column1: 1. Children looked after continuously for at least 12 months as at 31 March excluding those children in respite care.
2. Includes children looked after who attend primary, secondary and special schools (including CTC's and academies).

3.  This is the percentage of children looked after continuously for 12 months at 31 March who were aged 4-15 at the start of the academic year (31 August) and had a valid Unique Pupil Number (UPN) recorded in the SSDA903 return.

4. This is the number of children looked after continuously for at least 12 months at 31 March who were aged 4-15 at the start of the academic year (31 August) and were matched to the School Census. This is the denominator.
Figures for previous years may be different to previously published figures as LAs may update information for past years.
National and Regional figures have been rounded to the nearest 10. Local Authority figures have been rounded to the nearest 5.
Totals may not appear to equal the sum of component parts because numbers have been rounded.
x = number less than or equal to 5 or percentage where the numerator is less than or equal to 5 or the denominator is less than or equal to 10.
See technical note 18 for more information on rounding conventions.
